Code Explanation (Short & Easy)
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
Imports libraries:
pandas → used for data handling and tables.
seaborn → provides built-in datasets like Iris.
df = sns.load_dataset('iris')
Loads the famous Iris flower dataset into a DataFrame named df.
print(df.head())
Displays the first 5 rows of the dataset.
Helps us quickly inspect the data.
print(df.describe())
Generates overall summary statistics for numerical columns.
Shows:
count
mean
standard deviation
minimum value
maximum value
quartiles (25%, 50%, 75%)
grouped = df.groupby('species').describe()
Groups the data based on flower species:
setosa
versicolor
virginica
Then calculates statistics separately for each species.
print(grouped)
Prints the species-wise statistical summary.
